30/06/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Ahmet Necdet Sezer approved on Tuesday (29 June) the law amending the code of criminal procedure and abolishing the State Security Courts.
His approval is the final step in making the changes, intended to harmonise Turkish legislation with that of the EU, in preparation for launching accession negotiations with the Union.
(Anadolu Agency, NTV - 29/06/04)
